South Korea unveils combat ready Surion helicopters
2013-05-23 02:47:51 GMT
After six years of operational testing, South Korea's first homegrown combat helicopter, Surion, has been deemed ready for a battle by military officials.The project to build a two-engine transport utility helicopter was launched in 2006 by South Korea's Defense Acquisition and Procurement Agency.The Surion model is equipped with 3D electronic maps, automatic flying and vibration reduction systems, which the South Korean army said helped it pass 50 flight tests under extreme weather conditions in Alaska.The South Korean military said it plans to introduce about 200 more Surions by the end of 2022.(Agencies)
